<DOC><DOCNO> AP881222-0111 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-22-88 1321EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SAfrica-Attack     12-22 0128</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--SAfrica-Attack,0132</SECOND><HEAD>13 Injured In Grenade Attack</HEAD><DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A grenade exploded near a groupof people standing next to a police station near Cape Town, injuring13 people, including 10 policemen, authorities said.   Two children and one woman were hurt in the attack Wednesday,police said.   Police said the grenade was tossed from a moving vehicle inNyanga township, about 10 miles outside Cape Town. They did not givethe races of the victims, but most policemen in the township areblack.   Militant anti-apartheid activists consider black policemen to becollaborators with the white-led government and frequently targetthem for attack.   No one claimed responsibility for the attack, but police haveblamed most such incidents on the outlawed African National Congressguerrilla movement.</TEXT></DOC>